Date: Wed 8 Oct 2003
From: Joseph Dudley <jdudley@intellibridge.com>

Bird Migration and West Nile Virus Spread
-----------------------------------------
It is very interesting and enlightening to compare the animated map
of Common Grackle migrations and concentrations at:
<http://www.birdsource.org/GIS/images/cgrack_as96moani.gif>
with the animated map of the spread and distribution of West Nile
Virus in North America from 1999-2002 posted on the Cornell
Laboratory of Ornithology's website:
<http://environmentalrisk.cornell.edu/WNV/>.
--
Joseph P. Dudley, Ph.D.
Senior Analyst
