Date: Wed 8 Oct 2003
From: Jeanne Pfeiffer <Jeanne.Pfeiffer@co.hennepin.mn.us>

Influence of Water Abundance on West Nile Virus Spread in the
USA
--------------------------------------------------
I have found the patterns very interesting, because the states with
the most cases generally have the least free or standing water and
have actually had drought or fire danger warnings. That is true for
South Dakota and Colorado for sure. I think we should consider
that extreme dryness and its effect on the occurrence of disease.
Minnesota has a lot of water and many mosquitoes, yet didn't have
the numbers of cases one might expect for our available standing
water conditions. There may be other conditions that explain the
differences, however.
--
Jeanne Pfeiffer
<Jeanne.Pfeiffer@co.hennepin.mn.us>
